cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SE 

The paper proposes a machine learning-based system for transient stability assessment in power systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the modeling, analysis, and control of complex systems. The paper also utilizes machine learning methods, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category. The proposed system uses a long short-term memory network, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the gradual deployment of wide-area protection and control systems, which suggests the relevance of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves case studies, which may fall under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
